---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Draft Terms of Service for AEDIN's public site + paid API. The effective
// date is a placeholder until the paid API launches. NOTE (not legal advice):
// appropriate for self-serve Developer/Team tiers; institutional contracts
// ($5K/yr+) should get a licensing attorney's review before signing.
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for the AEDIN knowledge base, website, and API."
  noindex={true}
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-nature-900">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 mt-1"><strong class="text-nature-900">Effective date:</strong> TBD — set when paid API launches.</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">1. Acceptance of these terms</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the website at
      <a href="https://aedin.io" class="text-nature-700 hover:underline">aedin.io</a> and the AEDIN
      application programming interface (the "API"), collectively the "Service." By accessing or using the
      Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 mt-2">
      The Service is operated by Vivek LeBouef ("AEDIN," "we," "us," or "our"), an individual data
      engineer based in Guam, United States. If and when AEDIN is conducted through a registered legal
      entity, these Terms will be assigned to that entity and this paragraph will be updated.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">2. Definitions</h2>
    <dl class="text-sm text-earth-700 space-y-2 mt-2">
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-nature-900">Free Surface</dt>
        <dd class="ml-4">
          The publicly-accessible website at aedin.io, including all entity, claim, source, region, and
          interaction pages, the atlas and crop-web visualizations, and the unauthenticated Free API tier
          (limited to 100 requests per IP address per day).
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-nature-900">API</dt>
        <dd class="ml-4">
          The programmatic interface served from <code>api.aedin.io</code>, including the Free, Developer,
          Team, and Institutional tiers.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-nature-900">API Key</dt>
        <dd class="ml-4">
          An authentication credential issued to a Subscriber upon successful payment, used to authorize API requests.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-nature-900">Subscriber</dt>
        <dd class="ml-4">
          A person or entity who has signed up for and paid for a Developer, Team, or Institutional tier.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-nature-900">Records</dt>
        <dd class="ml-4">
          Any data returned by the API, including without limitation entity records, interaction claims,
          trait claims, source metadata, region metadata, GloBI-tier interactions, and the
          <code>source_attribution</code> objects attached to each.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">3. The Free Surface</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      You may browse, search, link to, and read the Free Surface without payment or account creation. We may
      impose IP-based rate limits on the unauthenticated Free API tier to protect service availability.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">4. Accounts</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      To subscribe to a paid tier, you must (a) provide a valid email address, (b) complete payment through
      our payment processor (Stripe), and (c) agree to these Terms. You are responsible for maintaining the
      confidentiality of your API Key(s) and for all activity that occurs under your account.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">5. License to access Records</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      Subject to your compliance with these Terms and payment of all applicable fees, AEDIN grants you a
      non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to query the API and to use Records in your
      applications, products, and research, including for commercial purposes.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">6. Attribution obligations</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      Records returned by the API are AEDIN-curated metadata layered over data sourced from third-party
      upstream providers (including but not limited to GloBI, GBIF, Wikidata, Trefle, USDA GRIN, Open-Meteo,
      and SoilGrids) and the open-access scientific literature. Each Record includes a
      <code>source_attribution</code> field describing its provenance.
    </p>
    <ol class="text-sm text-earth-700 list-decimal pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
      <li>
        You agree to preserve and surface the <code>source_attribution</code> object substantially as
        returned by the API when redistributing any Record to a third party, including but not limited to:
        rendering in a downstream user interface, including in a corpus for machine-learning training or
        evaluation, or re-publishing in any form.
      </li>
      <li>
        You agree to honor the attribution and license requirements of each named upstream source. The
        current catalogue of upstream sources and their citation guidance is published at
        <a href="/data-sources" class="text-nature-700 hover:underline">aedin.io/data-sources</a>
        and is incorporated by reference into these Terms.
      </li>
      <li>
        When citing AEDIN in academic work, please use the canonical citation published at
        <a href="/about" class="text-nature-700 hover:underline">aedin.io/about</a>.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">7. Restrictions</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">You will not, and will not permit others to:</p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-earth-700 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
      <li>Bulk-download or scrape the Free Surface or unauthenticated Free API tier to circumvent paid tier limits.</li>
      <li>Resell or sublicense raw Record access as a standalone service substantially similar to AEDIN's API without prior written agreement.</li>
      <li>Misrepresent AEDIN-derived Records as your own original research without appropriate attribution.</li>
      <li>Use the API in a manner that materially degrades availability for other Subscribers, including denial-of-service attacks, deliberate sustained over-quota requests, or use as an open proxy.</li>
      <li>Use the Service to create derivative datasets that strip the <code>source_attribution</code> field before redistribution.</li>
      <li>Use the Service in violation of applicable law, including without limitation export control, sanctions, or copyright law.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">8. Payment, renewal, and cancellation</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      Paid tiers are billed in advance through Stripe, monthly or annually depending on the tier selected.
      Subscriptions renew automatically until canceled. You may cancel at any time through the customer
      portal; cancellation takes effect at the end of the then-current billing period. Fees paid are
      non-refundable except where required by law.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 mt-2">
      AEDIN may change the pricing of any tier with at least 30 days' notice. Existing annual subscriptions
      remain at the price in effect at the start of the billing period for the duration of that period.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">9. Termination</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      You may terminate your account at any time. AEDIN may suspend or terminate your account for material
      breach of these Terms, including without limitation breach of §6 (Attribution) or §7 (Restrictions).
      For non-material breach, AEDIN will provide a reasonable opportunity to cure before suspension.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 mt-2">Sections 6, 7, 11, 12, 13, and 14 survive termination.</p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">10. Service availability</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      AEDIN operates the Service on a commercially reasonable best-efforts basis. We do not guarantee
      uninterrupted availability for the Free Surface or Developer / Team tiers. The Institutional tier may
      include a separately-negotiated Service Level Agreement; in the absence of an executed SLA, these Terms
      describe the full extent of our availability commitments.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">11. Warranty disclaimer</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 uppercase">
      The Service and all Records are provided "as is" and "as available," without warranty of any kind,
      express or implied, including without limitation warranties of merchantability, fitness for a
      particular purpose, non-infringement, or accuracy. Without limiting the foregoing, AEDIN does not
      warrant that individual Records are accurate, complete, or suitable for any particular application.
      Records are intended as references to primary sources; you are responsible for verifying Records
      against their cited primary sources before making decisions that depend on their accuracy.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">12. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700 uppercase">
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, AEDIN's total liability arising out of or relating
      to these Terms or your use of the Service will not exceed the amounts you paid to AEDIN in the twelve
      (12) months preceding the event giving rise to liability. In no event will AEDIN be liable for any
      indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">13. Indemnification</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless AEDIN from and against any third-party claims,
      damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or
      relating to: (a) your use of the Service in violation of these Terms, (b) your breach of §6
      (Attribution) or §7 (Restrictions), or (c) your applications or products that incorporate Records.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">14. Governing law and disputes</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the Territory of Guam, United States, without regard to its
      conflict-of-laws principles. Any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms will be resolved
      exclusively in the courts of Guam, and you consent to the personal jurisdiction of those courts.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">15. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      AEDIN may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be announced via email to
      active Subscribers at least 30 days before taking effect. Continued use of the Service after the
      effective date of an update constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-nature-900 mt-8 mb-2">16. Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth-700">
      Questions about these Terms may be directed to
      <a href="mailto:contact@aedin.io" class="text-nature-700 hover:underline">contact@aedin.io</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
